text.*:

Lac Ichkeul

The number of Ramsar sites in Tunisia are 41 sites in 2015, which have in total 840,363 hectares of land coverage.[1] Tunisia is part of the Ramsar Convention from 1980 and has many Wetlands such as Chott el Jerid and Ichkeul Lake, as well as others.
